+# Slice 11 — Crews & roles — Implementation Plan
+
+> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.
+
+**Goal:** Add a CrewAI-style role/task/process layer — define-your-own role/goal/backstory members, a task list with optional typed output + dependency context, and two processes (sequential, hierarchical) — as a thin layer that *compiles onto* the existing Slice-10 workflow engine and the agents-as-tools orchestrator.
+
+**Architecture:** A crew is a plain TS object (`defineCrew({ id, members, tasks, process })`). Members become role-bearing `Agent`s (role/goal/backstory composed into the system prompt; model resolved live by the existing selector). A **sequential** crew compiles to a `WorkflowDef` and runs on the Slice-10 engine unchanged; a **hierarchical** crew reuses `createOrchestrator` + an auto-built manager. `runCrew` dispatches by process under a `crew.run` telemetry span; `bun run crew <name>` is the CLI over a `crews/` registry. No new execution engine, no parallel structured-output system, no memory (deferred to Slice 12).
+
+**Tech Stack:** TypeScript + Bun · Vercel AI SDK `ai@^6.0.217` (`ToolSet`, `LanguageModel`) · `zod@^4.4.3` (optional per-task output schema) · existing `src/workflow/*` (engine), `src/core/orchestrator.ts` + `delegate.ts` (`runGuardedAgent`), `src/telemetry/spans.ts`, `src/run/run-store.ts` · `bun test` + `MockLanguageModelV3` + `registerTestProvider`.
+
+## Global Constraints
+
+- **Always `bun`, never `npm`.** `bun run typecheck`, `bun test`, `bun run lint` (biome, `preset: "recommended"`).
+- **Prefer `enum` over string-literal unions** for finite named sets (string enums only, e.g. `enum CrewProcess { Sequential = 'sequential' }`). Prefer `type` over `interface`. Early returns; small focused files; descriptive names.
+- **Don't hardcode model choices/budgets/limits** — members declare `requires`/`prefer`; the model is resolved LIVE by the existing selector via `onBeforeDelegate`. Env vars are fallback-only. Reuse `runGuardedAgent` (Slice-9 depth + return cap) — do NOT add new guardrail code.
+- **No new execution engine.** Sequential MUST compile to a `WorkflowDef` and run via the existing `runWorkflow`; hierarchical MUST reuse `createOrchestrator`/`runOrchestrator`. Reuse zod I/O (Slice-10 `safeParse`), not a new structured-output system.
+- **Documentation hard line:** this slice MUST add a "Crews & roles" section to `docs/architecture.md` or `bun run docs:check` (pre-commit) fails. `bun run setup` activates hooks once.
+- **No `console.log`** except the CLI's intentional user-facing output in `crew.ts` `main()`. No commit without clean `bun run typecheck`.
+- **Telemetry-by-default:** a `crew.run` root span; the existing `workflow.run/workflow.step` (sequential) and `agent.delegation` (hierarchical) spans nest beneath it.
+- New error type extends `FrameworkError` (`src/core/errors.ts`); `name` is set automatically via `new.target.name` — do not set it manually.
+- **Memory is out of scope** (Slice 12). Do not add any vector store / persistence.
